  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the alternatives to WalkMe?",
  "response": "WalkMe is a popular digital adoption platform that helps guide users through software and websites with interactive walkthroughs and on-screen guidance. If you're looking for alternatives to WalkMe, here are several options that offer similar functionalities:\n\n1. **Whatfix**:\n   - Whatfix provides in-app guidance, interactive walkthroughs, and task lists to help users navigate and master software applications. It's known for its user-friendly interface and robust analytics.\n\n2. **Userlane**:\n   - Userlane offers on-screen interactive guides and tooltips to help users learn and use software efficiently. It's particularly favored for its ease of use and customization options.\n\n3. **Pendo**:\n   - Pendo focuses on product engagement and user feedback, offering in-app guides, NPS surveys, and detailed analytics. It's widely used for enhancing user experience and driving product adoption.\n\n4. **Appcues**:\n   - Appcues allows you to create and manage user onboarding experiences with customizable modals, tooltips, and hotspots. It's a good choice for SaaS companies looking to improve user engagement.\n\n5. **Chameleon**:\n   - Chameleon provides tools for creating in-product tours, tooltips, and surveys to guide users and gather feedback. It's known for its flexibility and integration capabilities.\n\n6. **Inline Manual**:\n   - Inline Manual offers contextual help, walkthroughs, and user guides to improve user experience and software adoption. It's praised for its detailed analytics and reporting features.\n\n7. **UserGuiding**:\n   - UserGuiding helps you create interactive product tours, tooltips, and checklists to onboard and educate users. It's noted for its affordability and ease of setup.\n\n8. **Gainsight PX**:\n   - Gainsight PX (formerly Aptrinsic) focuses on product experience management, offering user onboarding, feature adoption, and product analytics. It's popular among B2B software companies.\n\nEach of these alternatives has its own unique features and strengths, so the best choice for you will depend on your specific needs, budget, and the type of software or website you're looking to enhance.",
